lt silly not having known it last night, so rather than allow others to get in that position, here is a post we will use to publish useful Shaman tactics on large raids. This is my two bits, I'll hope the other Master Shaman will place further info here for you. <p><br><font color=Red><b>Onker Purdydense<br> Level 51 Mojo Troll<br><center><font color=orange><b> Master Of Descending Darkness(DD)<br><font color=yellow>The Biggest b00bs on Zeb</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ujonnwinterstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jonn Winterstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#660000>(3/24/02 5:33:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Lessons, from those who know.</span><hr size=1> Don't buff rangers, they get their own and just gonna die anyway...lol<br><br>Good post tho Onker, easier for tanks to get aggro if they can stand and beat on a mob, instead of chasing you around<br><br>Jonn Winterstorm<br>55 Luminary <p><img src="http://jonnwinterstorm.itgo.com/JonnSig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usaavakspiritwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saavak Spiritwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Da Kitty</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#660000>(3/25/02 9:58:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Lessons, from those who know.</span><hr size=1> /glares at Onker<br><br>So.....You were the one always making me ha